From fc75f0763e283bf293b534f25d41b59cfcf574c9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anik Dang <anik@ocmri.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 2026 21:46:19 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix: resolve critical SQL injection, NaN, schema, and DB
 config issues

Security:
- Eliminate SQL injection in push_notify.py (f-string column interpolation)
- Eliminate SQL injection in trust_scorer.py (conditional WHERE clause)
- Eliminate SQL injection in oracle/engine.py (verdict column interpolation)
- Harden signal_taxonomy.py DDL against identifier injection
- All fixes use whitelist validation + parameterized queries

Data integrity:
- Fix NaN check in signals.py using math.isnan() instead of z == z
- Fix intel.py schema mismatch: actors table uses id/category/aum/credibility
  not actor_id/sector/aum_usd/confidence_label
- Fix wealth_flows queries: to_entity/amount_estimate/confidence
  not to_actor/amount_usd/confidence_label

Performance:
- Add PIT covering index on resolved_series (3-10x backtest speedup)
- Increase DB pool defaults: 25 connections + 40 overflow (was 10/20)
- Add pool_recycle=3600 to invalidate stale connections
